paragraphs.title: Load 2007Property data into table with PySpark
paragraphs.text:
%pyspark
from pyspark.sql import SQLContext, Row
# sqlContext = SQLContext(sc)

# Load a text file and convert each line to a Row.
lines = sc.textFile("file:///home/pitt/mke_data/MPROP2007DEC.csv")
fields = lines.map(lambda l: l.split(","))
propValue = fields.map(lambda p: Row(propid=p[0], totalpropvalue=int(p[16]), proptype=p[12]))

# Infer the schema, and register the DataFrame as a table.
schemaProperty = sqlContext.createDataFrame(propValue)
schemaProperty.registerTempTable("property2007")

paragraphs.text:
%sql 
select  propId, propValue, propType, neighborhood, basement, attic, bldgArea, age, 
numFireplace, ac, bedroom, bathroom, halfBath, parkingType, lotArea
from property2005 where propType='1' and age between ${m1Age}  and ${m2Age}  limit 1000

%sql
-- combine the two into result set using sql. calculate the change in value from 2007 to 2005 as the left-most variable.
select (p7.totalpropvalue - p5.propValue) as valuechange, p5.propType, p5.neighborhood, p5.basement, p5.attic, p5.bldgArea, 
p5.age, p5.numFireplace, p5.ac, p5.bedroom, p5.bathroom, p5.halfBath, p5.parkingType, p5.lotArea
from property2005 p5 
join property2007 p7 on (p5.propId = p7.propid and p5.propType = p7.proptype)
where p5.propType='1' and age between 3 and 500 limit 1000

%sql
select p5.neighborhood, round(avg(p7.totalpropvalue - p5.propValue),0) as valuechange, 
count(p7.totalpropvalue) as cnt
from property2005 p5 
join property2007 p7 on (p5.propId = p7.propid and p5.propType = p7.proptype)
where p5.propType='1' and age between 3 and 500 
group by p5.neighborhood
order by valuechange desc 
limit 10
